        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="1166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.633/4–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-15T19:00:00-05:00">April 15, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>213. Immediately following tel<note n="42" xml:id="d1166fn42">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> requests you make further approach
                    Commies re Mukden. If you feel recent joint approach you and ur colleagues re
                    consular facilities Peiping (urtel 611 Apr 14<note n="43" xml:id="d1166fn43">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1077">p. 1077</ref>.</note>)
                    makes desirable deferring Mukden issue few days or a week Dept would have no
                    objection thereto but desires be informed thereof.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
